definition.value: A bile acid glycine conjugate having cholic acid as the bile acid component.
A composition-only glycan consisting of six hexosyl groups, three 2-acetaminohexosyl groups and one 6-deoxyhexosyl group (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex6 HexNAc3 dHex1.
A composition-only glycan consisting of five hexosyl groups, one 2-acetaminohexosyl group and one 6-deoxyhexosyl group (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex5 HexNAc1 dHex1.

A composition-only glycan consisting of five hexosyl groups, four 2-acetaminohexosyl groups, three 6-deoxyhexosyl group and one N-acetyl-neuraminic acid group (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex5 HexNAc4 dHex3 NeuAc1.
A composition-only glycan consisting of four hexosyl groups, two 2-acetaminohexosyl groups and three 6-deoxyhexosyl groups (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex4 HexNAc2 dHex3.
A 3-(1-methylpyrrolidin-2-yl)pyridine in which the chiral centre has S-configuration. The naturally occurring and most active enantiomer of nicotine, isolated from Nicotiana tabacum.

A linear amino hexasaccharide comprising a (2->3), (1->4), (1->3), (1->4), (1->3) sequence of alpha-N-acetylneuramine, beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine, beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine and (at the reducing end) N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine.
A 4-p-coumaroylquinic acid in which the double bond adopts a trans-configuration.
A phosphosphingolipid consisting of sphingosine having a phosphocholine moiety attached to its primary hydroxyl group.
C-14 demethylated eburicol

A member of the class of pyrazoles that is 1H-pyrazole substituted by 2-fluoro-6-(trifluoromethyl)benzyl and (2,6-difluorobenzoyl)amino groups at positions 1 and 3, respectively. It is a inhibitor of Ca(2+) release-activated Ca(2+) (CRAC) channel and inhibits the release of mast cell mediators and T-cell cytokines in human and rat preparations.

A monoazo compound that is a photoisomerizable analogue of GSK-5498A. It is a Ca2+ release-activated Ca2+ (CRAC) channel inhibitor which exists in the trans-configuration in the dark (415nm) and in the cis-configuration under 365 nm illumination.

A carbohydrate acid derivative anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of any N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminosyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminide; major species at pH 7.3.
Any steroid carrying a 14alpha-hydroxymethyl substituent.
Any 14-formyl steroid in which the formyl group at position 14 has alpha- configuration.
Any steroid carrying a 14alpha-dihydroxymethyl substituent.
A 2'-deoxyribonucleoside 3'-monophosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 2'-deoxyuridine 3'-monophosphate (3'-dUMP); major species at pH 7.3.
The trans isomer of piCRAC-1.
The cis isomer of piCRAC-1.
Any O-acylcarnitine in which the carnitine component has L-configuration and the acyl group is a fatty acid.
Any O-acylcarnitine in which the acyl group is a fatty acid and the carnitine component has configuration undefined.
A non-proteinogenic alpha-amino acid in which benzene is ortho-fused onto the C-3-C-4 bond of L-proline.
